The former Generations actor fought back tears as he recounted the fond memories he had of his friend. Menzi had to pause during his speech as tears streamed down his eyes. When I heard about Sfiso s passing I really could not believe it he said.Menzi said that when Mzwakhe Mbuli called him with the news of Sfiso's death, he put the phone down in disbelief. The actor burst into tears as he told mourners how he gave Sfiso his suit for his first album cover shoot. I m sorry Ayanda. Hamba kahle Ncwane hamba kahle he said. It has been an emotionally-charged Saturday morning as the entire nation unites in grief to bid farewell to gospel star Sfiso Ncwane.Numerous high-profile personalities including Malusi and Norma Gigaba Khaya Mthethwa Rebecca Malope and former SABC COO Hlaudi Motsoeneng have also attended to pay their last respects.Actor Menzi Ngubane becomes emotional as he recounts the moment he learnt of #sfisoncwane death #RipSfiso #Ncwane #SfisoNcwanefuneral pic.twitter.com/IqBeIk5OAe Menzi Ngubane takes to the stage to cheers from the crowd #SfisoNcwanefuneral #sfisoncwane #RipSfisoNcwane pic.twitter.com/Jez4u7xNlU The late gospel icons children comfort Ayanda #SfisoNcwanefuneral #sfisoncwane #RipSfisoNcwane pic.twitter.com/hGYf1eFPku 